<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  ============================================================================
  XBRL Calculation Linkbase  (Calc 1.0 scaffold, with Calc 1.1 notes)
  ============================================================================

  PURPOSE

  Vendor-neutral, regulator-neutral scaffold for a minimal but valid
  calculation linkbase. Replace the `ext:` concepts and the schema href
  with the actual extension namespace and schema filename.

  AUTHORITATIVE REFERENCES

  * XBRL 2.1 Recommendation (2003-12-31, errata-corrected 2013-02-20)
      Section 5.2.5  "The calculation linkbase"
      https://www.xbrl.org/Specification/XBRL-2.1/REC-2003-12-31/
        XBRL-2.1-REC-2003-12-31+corrected-errata-2013-02-20.html
  * XBRL Calculations 1.1 Recommendation (2023-02-22)
      https://www.xbrl.org/Specification/calculation-1.1/REC-2023-02-22/
        calculation-1.1-REC-2023-02-22.html

  ============================================================================
  CALC 1.0  (XBRL 2.1, summation-item)
  ============================================================================

  * arcrole (verbatim, http, NOT https):
      http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/summation-item
  * Semantics: a parent fact equals the SIGNED sum (weight x child fact)
    of its child facts that share the SAME contextRef, SAME unitRef, and
    therefore the same period and entity. Facts in different contexts do
    NOT participate in the same summation.
  * Weight attribute is xs:decimal. Canonical values are +1 and -1; values
    other than +/- 1 are permitted by the spec but rare and discouraged.
    Use -1 to subtract a child from the parent (e.g. cost-of-sales from
    revenue to derive gross profit).
  * Decimals/precision interaction: Calc 1.0 inconsistencies are evaluated
    by deriving an INTERVAL from each fact's @decimals or @precision (the
    open interval around the reported value within which the true value
    must lie) and checking whether the parent's interval contains the
    weighted summation interval of its children. A reported parent value
    within the children's combined interval is consistent. (XBRL 2.1
    sec. 5.2.5.2.) The "least precise child" heuristic that some legacy
    tooling uses is an approximation; the normative rule is the interval
    test.
  * Duplicate-fact gotcha. Distinguish two cases.
      P-equal duplicates: facts for the same concept that share BOTH
        contextRef and unitRef and report the SAME value (subject to
        decimals/precision compatibility). These are legal under XBRL
        2.1 sec. 4.10 and do not break calc.
      V-inconsistent duplicates: same concept, same context/unit, but
        DIFFERENT values (or values whose decimals intervals do not
        overlap). These cause the consuming calc network to report an
        inconsistency on every summation that touches the concept, and
        must be eliminated before validation.
  * Regulator support:
      SEC EDGAR (EFM):                 Calc 1.0 only.
      ESMA ESEF:                       Calc 1.0 (Calc 1.1 not yet mandated).
      UK FRC / Companies House / HMRC: Calc 1.0.
      Dutch SBR / KvK / AFM:           Calc 1.0.
    Always confirm with the regulator's current Filer Manual or Reporting
    Manual before adopting Calc 1.1 in production filings.

  ============================================================================
  CALC 1.1  (Calculations 1.1, REC 2023-02-22)
  ============================================================================

  * Spec namespace (informational, used in roleType / arcroleType decls):
      https://xbrl.org/2023/calculation-1.1
  * NEW arcrole introduced by Calc 1.1 (verbatim, https):
      https://xbrl.org/2023/arcrole/summation-item
    NOTE: This is a DIFFERENT arcrole from Calc 1.0 (https vs http, and a
    new path). The element used on the wire is still link:calculationArc.
  * A Calc 1.1 network and a Calc 1.0 network are independent and MUST be
    validated separately. Mixing the two arcroles within one ELR is allowed
    but each network is processed under its own rules. Note: a Calc 1.1
    capable processor MAY (per Calc 1.1 sec. 1.2) optionally apply Calc 1.1
    semantics to a Calc 1.0 (summation-item) network as well; this is
    implementation defined and should not be relied upon.
  * Key difference: Calc 1.1 supports cross-context summation by reasoning
    about period/aggregation duration, allowing roll-forwards and segment
    aggregations that Calc 1.0 cannot express. It also redefines rounding
    semantics for inconsistency detection.
  * When to choose:
      Stay on Calc 1.0 for any filing destined for a regulator that has
      not explicitly endorsed Calc 1.1.
      Use Calc 1.1 for internal pipelines or for taxonomies that have
      opted in (e.g. some IFRS Foundation experimental work).
      If unsure: ship Calc 1.0. It is universal.

  ============================================================================
  THIS FILE
  ============================================================================

  * Active scaffold uses Calc 1.0 (universal, regulator-safe).
  * Commented-out Calc 1.1 example at the bottom of the calculationLink
    is reference only.
  * Custom ELR `http://example.com/role/IncomeStatement` MUST be declared
    via link:roleType in the extension schema. The link:roleRef below
    resolves that roleType.
  * Concept locators reference `extension-schema.xsd`. Update the filename
    and concept QName fragments for the actual taxonomy.
-->
<link:linkbase
    xmlns:link="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/linkbase"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/linkbase
                        http://www.xbrl.org/2003/xbrl-linkbase-2003-12-31.xsd">

  <!--
    roleRef: resolves the custom ELR xlink:role used on the calculationLink
    below. The href must point to a link:roleType roleURI declaration
    inside the extension schema.
  -->
  <link:roleRef
      roleURI="http://example.com/role/IncomeStatement"
      xlink:type="simple"
      xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#IncomeStatement"/>

  <!--
    Calculation network for the Income Statement ELR.
    Parent:   ext:OperatingProfit
    Children: ext:Revenue          (weight = +1, additive)
              ext:OtherIncome      (weight = +1, additive)
              ext:CostOfSales      (weight = -1, subtractive)
              ext:OperatingExpense (weight = -1, subtractive)
    Semantics:
      OperatingProfit = Revenue + OtherIncome - CostOfSales - OperatingExpense
  -->
  <link:calculationLink
      xlink:type="extended"
      xlink:role="http://example.com/role/IncomeStatement">

    <!-- Locators: one per concept participating in the network. -->
    <link:loc xlink:type="locator"
              xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_OperatingProfit"
              xlink:label="OperatingProfit"/>
    <link:loc xlink:type="locator"
              xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_Revenue"
              xlink:label="Revenue"/>
    <link:loc xlink:type="locator"
              xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_OtherIncome"
              xlink:label="OtherIncome"/>
    <link:loc xlink:type="locator"
              xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_CostOfSales"
              xlink:label="CostOfSales"/>
    <link:loc xlink:type="locator"
              xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_OperatingExpense"
              xlink:label="OperatingExpense"/>

    <!--
      Additive arc: Revenue contributes +1 to OperatingProfit.
      `use` and `priority` are shown explicitly here for completeness;
      defaults are use="optional" and priority="0".
    -->
    <link:calculationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/summation-item"
        xlink:from="OperatingProfit"
        xlink:to="Revenue"
        order="1"
        weight="1"
        use="optional"
        priority="0"/>

    <!-- Additive arc: OtherIncome contributes +1. -->
    <link:calculationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/summation-item"
        xlink:from="OperatingProfit"
        xlink:to="OtherIncome"
        order="2"
        weight="1"/>

    <!-- Subtractive arc: CostOfSales contributes -1 (demonstrates negation). -->
    <link:calculationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/summation-item"
        xlink:from="OperatingProfit"
        xlink:to="CostOfSales"
        order="3"
        weight="-1"/>

    <!-- Subtractive arc: OperatingExpense contributes -1. -->
    <link:calculationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/summation-item"
        xlink:from="OperatingProfit"
        xlink:to="OperatingExpense"
        order="4"
        weight="-1"/>

    <!--
      ========================================================================
      CALC 1.1 EXAMPLE (commented out; do not enable for SEC/ESEF/SBR/HMRC)
      ========================================================================

      To opt in to Calc 1.1, change the arcrole on the calculationArc to the
      new https URI. The element name (link:calculationArc) does NOT change.
      A processor that supports Calc 1.1 will recognise the new arcrole and
      apply Calc 1.1 semantics; a Calc 1.0-only processor will ignore arcs
      with this arcrole, so the network becomes invisible to it.

      To advertise that the linkbase contains Calc 1.1 relationships,
      taxonomy authors should add an arcroleRef whose href points DIRECTLY
      at the published Calc 1.1 schema URI (do NOT fabricate a local
      arcroleType in your extension schema . the canonical declaration
      lives at xbrl.org). For example:

        link:arcroleRef
            arcroleURI="https://xbrl.org/2023/arcrole/summation-item"
            xlink:type="simple"
            xlink:href="https://xbrl.org/2023/calculation-1.1.xsd#summation-item"

      And the equivalent of the Revenue arc above would then be:

        link:calculationArc
            xlink:type="arc"
            xlink:arcrole="https://xbrl.org/2023/arcrole/summation-item"
            xlink:from="OperatingProfit"
            xlink:to="Revenue"
            order="1"
            weight="1"

      Reminder: Calc 1.0 and Calc 1.1 networks are validated independently.
      Do not assume a Calc 1.0 processor will silently upgrade.
    -->

  </link:calculationLink>
</link:linkbase>
